tourBios.exmtStatus: Exempt - Finished 11-45 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament (exempt to second reshuffle)
tourBios.curYearHigh: Won his only start on the Swing Thought Tour at Firewheel Golf Park - Bridges Course by five shots over Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament participant Hunter Hamrick...Shot 65-66 in the 36-hole event...Firewheel Golf Park was also a Web.com Tour Q School first stage host site, where Jones finished in solo fifth to advance.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Four-time state champion in high school...Won the UTSA Oak Hills Invitational individual title in three consecutive years at Baylor University (2013-2015)...Named to 2014 All-Big 12 Men's Golf Team...Named 2014 All-American Honorable Mention...Named to 2015 Big 12 All-Tournament Team...Named to 2015 All-Big 12 Men's Golf Team...Selected as a member of the 2015 U.S. Palmer Cup Team...Finished his career at Baylor with twelve top-5 finishes.
tourBios.personal: Attended Snowflake High School in Snowflake, Ariz., which he cites as his hometown...Once met President George W. Bush when he was practicing in Waco...Lists the Arizona Diamondbacks and Cleveland Cavaliers as his favorite professional teams...Would try to be a professional baseball player if he did not play golf...Would like to get involved with Children's Hospitals during his professional career.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour in 2016 is T23rd at the Club Colombia Championship Presented by Claro.
